The subject of police brutality and racism received national attention
following the airing of the videotaped beating of Rodney King by four
Los Angeles Policemen back in March.

In other cities across the country, recent reports of police brutality
and tense race relations have occurred in Chicago, Kansas City, and
Minneapolis.</SUM>
